org.projecthaystack.auth

Class AuthScheme

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.projecthaystack.auth.AuthScheme
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BasicScheme, Folio2Scheme, HmacScheme, ScramScheme

    public abstract class AuthScheme
extends Object
    AuthScheme is the base class for modeling pluggable authentication algorithms.

      • onClient

        public abstract AuthMsg onClient(AuthClientContext cx,
                                 AuthMsg msg)
        Handle a standardized client authentication challenge message from the server using RFC 7235.
        Parameters:
        cx - the current AuthClientContext
        msg - the AuthMsg sent by the server
        Returns:
        The AuthMsg to send back to the server to authenticate

      • onClientSuccess

        public void onClientSuccess(AuthClientContext cx,
                            AuthMsg msg)
        Callback after successful authentication with the server. The default implementation is a no-op.
        Parameters:
        cx - the current AuthClientContext
        msg - the AuthMsg sent by the server when it authenticated the client.

      • onClientNonStd

        public boolean onClientNonStd(AuthClientContext cx,
                              HttpURLConnection resp,
                              String content)
        Handle non-standardized client authentication when the standard process (RFC 7235) fails. If this scheme thinks it can handle the given response by sniffing the response code and headers, then it should process and return true.
        Parameters:
        cx - the current AuthClientContext
        resp - the response message from the server
        content - the body of the response if it had one, or null.
        Returns:
        true if the scheme processed the response, false otherwise. Returns false by default.
